    Inverse slicing and plotting

    from georeader import plot
from georeader.geotensor import GeoTensor
from georeader import save
from georeader import vectorize
import os
import numpy as np

s2url = "https://huggingface.co/datasets/isp-uv-es/WorldFloodsv2/resolve/main/test/S2/EMSR264_18MIANDRIVAZODETAIL_DEL_v2.tif"
filelocal = os.path.basename(s2url)
if not os.path.exists(filelocal):
    s2img = GeoTensor.load_file(s2url)
    save.save_tiled_geotiff(s2img, filelocal)
else:
    s2img = GeoTensor.load_file(filelocal)

# Set nodata value to zero
s2img.fill_value_default = 0
s2img = s2img.pad(((0,0), (25, 25), (10, 10)))

rgb = (s2img[[3,2,1]] / 3_500).clip(0,1)
plot.show(rgb)

    brightness = np.mean(rgb_slice, axis=0)
bright_clouds = brightness &gt;=.9
clouds_vect = vectorize.get_polygons(bright_clouds)
clouds_vect

    import geopandas as gpd
ax = plot.show(rgb_slice, bounds_in_latlng=True)
clouds_gpd = gpd.GeoDataFrame(geometry=clouds_vect, crs=rgb_slice.crs)
plot.add_shape_to_plot(clouds_gpd, 
                       kwargs_geopandas_plot={"color": "red"}, ax=ax)

    from georeader import read
rgb_slice_rev = rgb[:, slice(300,20,-1), slice(50,340)]
rgb_slice_rev
ax = plot.show(rgb_slice_rev, bounds_in_latlng=False)
bright_clouds_rev = read.read_reproject_like(bright_clouds, rgb_slice_rev)
plot.show(bright_clouds_rev, mask=True, vmax=1)
